                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/7678.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador to Brazil</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-06-02T18:00:00-03:06">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 2, 1913—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Acting Minister for Foreign Affairs assured me this afternoon that Brazil would
                    withhold recognition of Mexico until our course had been determined.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
